### 1.2 High missing malue features filtering

To ensure the statistical power of downstream differential analysis, a multi-stage missing value filtering strategy was applied at the **{{ high_mv_feature_filtering.pipeline_params.filtering_level }}** level. 

The filtering process strictly adhered to a sample-wise tolerance of **{{ "%.1f"|format(high_mv_feature_filtering.pipeline_params.thresholds.sample_mv_tol * 100) }}%**. 

Features were categorized into Missing At Random (MAR) and Missing Not At Random (MNAR) based on their distribution patterns across groups and QC samples. Specifically, the pipeline utilized a group-wise MNAR tolerance of **{{ "%.1f"|format(high_mv_feature_filtering.pipeline_params.thresholds.mnar_group_tol * 100) }}%** and a QC-specific tolerance of **{{ "%.1f"|format(high_mv_feature_filtering.pipeline_params.thresholds.mnar_qc_tol * 100) }}%** to prevent the premature loss of potentially biologically significant biomarkers that exhibit group-specific presence.

